<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,152,532]" pageId="18" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,428,454]" pageId="18" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[557,657,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="52">concilio</emphasis>
, unite separate parts into a whole, connect; in reference to the plesiomorphic features of this genus that link 
<emphasis box="[687,845,467,492]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="52">Chimeromyia</emphasis>
with other basal Eremoneura.
</paragraph>
